  "doc_id": "55110",
  "text": "Phase relationships between GPi and STN are open to several interpretations. However, we would choose to view them in the light of current models of the basal ganglia [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Off levodopa, activity in GPi led that in STN at ϳ20 Hz. This would be consistent with the common driving of STN and GPi by globus pallidus externa (GPe) (with conduction and neuronal delays to STN being longer than to GPi). Also off levodopa, activity in STN at ϳ6 Hz led that in GPi and might contribute to the postulated synchronization of output from GPi at low frequency in untreated Parkinson's disease [CITATION_6] .",
